 what? I made my first meal ever—pork schnitzel! I didn’t think it would be much different from cooking anything else, but there’s a lot more to it than just frying up some meat. Here’s how it went down.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-ec64" data-pf-type="Section" id="text_image" class="sc-iapVNj iUWSoH pf-30_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dExXmK cexqoG"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-31_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:5px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-32_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-33_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-34_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1729863949" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1729863949 1536w" width="1200" height="1600" alt="How to prepare schnitzel meat for perfect pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How to prepare schnitzel meat for perfect pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-35_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-36_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Finding out about schnitzel</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-41_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">When my dad asked me if I’d ever had schnitzel, I realised I’d only tried the chicken kind. Pork schnitzel is famous in Austria (who knew?), but it’s super different from chicken schnitzel. So, I decided to try and see if I could make it just right.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-43_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">Getting the pork ready - Hammer time</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-47_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first thing I had to do was prep the pork. I learned that you must pound it really thin with a wooden mallet – like you’re hammering a nail but with more focus! I didn’t want to hit it too hard and accidentally tear the meat, so I had to balance it right. Flattening the pork is supposed to make it tender, and it felt fantastic to see the piece get bigger and thinner as I worked on it. Then, I added some salt and pepper to bring out the flavour. Prepping the pork was already feeling like a workout!</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-49_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_pork_schnitzel_cooking_at_home_A_step-by-step_guide_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863231" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_pork_schnitzel_cooking_at_home_A_step-by-step_guide_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863231 1536w" width="540" height="720" alt="Mastering pork schnitzel cooking at home A step-by-step guide - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering pork schnitzel cooking at home A step-by-step guide - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-50_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-53_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-54_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863476" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863476 1536w" width="1000" height="1000" alt="Easy pork schnitzel recipe for first-time cooks - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Easy pork schnitzel recipe for first-time cooks - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-55_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-56_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Making it crunchy – The three-step coating process</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This was probably my favourite part – making the schnitzel coating! The recipe calls for a three-step coating process to get that famous schnitzel crunch. First, I coated the pork in flour, which helped the next layer stick. Then, I dunked it into a bowl of beaten eggs, making sure every part was covered. Finally, I rolled it in breadcrumbs, pressing them in to ensure they stayed put. The breadcrumbs make the schnitzel crispy and crunchy, and I was already imagining the sound it would make when I bit into it!</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-63_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-64_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-65_ pf-heading-1-h3">Frying and oven finishing for perfect cooking</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-67_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With the pork all coated, it was time to fry! The recipe mentioned avocado oil, but we only had olive oil, so I went with that. I heated the oil in a pan until it sizzled, then carefully placed the schnitzel. It started to bubble and crackle right away, which was so satisfying! Frying each side took a few minutes to get golden brown, but to ensure it was cooked all the way through, we finished it in the oven. Since pork has to be fully cooked, this extra oven time was necessary for safety (and also for extra crispiness!).</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-69_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Your_step-by-step_guide_to_delicious_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863535" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Your_step-by-step_guide_to_delicious_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863535 1536w" width="540" height="720" alt="Your step-by-step guide to delicious pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Your step-by-step guide to delicious pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-70_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-71_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-73_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-74_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Best_beginner_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_a_crispy_finish_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863592" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Best_beginner_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_a_crispy_finish_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863592 1536w" width="540" height="720" alt="Best beginner pork schnitzel recipe for a crispy finish - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Best beginner pork schnitzel recipe for a crispy finish - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-75_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-76_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-78_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-79_ pf-heading-1-h3">Choosing sides, including potatoes</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-81_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Once the schnitzel was ready, it was time to think about sides. My family chose boiled potatoes and green vegetables, along with a parsley sauce on the side. If I could choose, I’d probably go for fries or mashed potatoes, but I figured I’d give boiled potatoes a try. The green vegetables were a nice pop of colour, and the parsley sauce added a bit of freshness. To be honest, I don’t remember much about the sauce (I was too focused on the schnitzel), but it was fun to try something different.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-83_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-84_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-85_ pf-heading-1-h3">Final rating - The good, the crispy, and the could-be-crispier</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-87_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Looking back, I’d give my first pork schnitzel experience a solid eight out of ten. It turned out nice and crispy on the outside, but if I’m honest, I think it could’ve been even crispier. The flavour was pretty good, and I was happy with the seasoning, but I think I’d change a few things next time. For one, I’d probably plan my ingredients a little better to avoid last-minute changes, like switching out avocado oil for olive oil. And if I get to pick the sides, I’d definitely go for fries or mashed potatoes – much more my style!</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-89_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Homemade_schnitzel_tips_for_a_crunchy_golden_coating_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863683" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Homemade_schnitzel_tips_for_a_crunchy_golden_coating_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863683 1536w" width="540" height="720" alt="Homemade schnitzel tips for a crunchy, golden coating - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Homemade schnitzel tips for a crunchy, golden coating - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-90_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-91_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-93_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-94_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_Make_Pork_Schnitzel_at_Home_Simple_steps_for_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863071" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_Make_Pork_Schnitzel_at_Home_Simple_steps_for_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863071 1536w" width="540" height="720" alt="How to Make Pork Schnitzel at Home – Simple steps for success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How to Make Pork Schnitzel at Home – Simple steps for success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-95_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-96_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-98_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-99_ pf-heading-1-h3">Lessons learned and what’s next</h3><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-101_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Cooking schnitzel was a lot of fun, even though it was more work than expected. From pounding the pork to carefully coating each piece and then frying it, every step felt like a little victory. Next time, I’d focus on preparing everything before starting and maybe experiment with different oils or make chicken schnitzel to compare. I still have much to learn in the kitchen, but this was a pretty awesome start. </p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-e3e4" data-pf-type="Section" id="pf-84621b23--copy-of-text_image" class="sc-iapVNj iUWSoH pf-103_ pf-color-scheme-1 pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dExXmK cexqoG"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-104_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-lg:5px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-105_"><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-106_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-107_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-108_ pf-heading-1-h3">Finding out about schnitzel</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1729863949" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.jpg?v=1729863949 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.jpg?v=1729863949 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_prepare_schnitzel_meat_for_perfect_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.jpg?v=1729863949 320w" width="1200" height="1600" alt="How to prepare schnitzel meat for perfect pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How to prepare schnitzel meat for perfect pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-110_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-111_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-113_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">When my dad asked me if I’d ever had schnitzel, I realised I’d only tried the chicken kind. Pork schnitzel is famous in Austria (who knew?), but it’s super different from chicken schnitzel. So, I decided to try and see if I could make it just right.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-115_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-116_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-117_ pf-heading-1-h3">Getting the pork ready - Hammer time</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_pork_schnitzel_cooking_at_home_A_step-by-step_guide_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863231" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_pork_schnitzel_cooking_at_home_A_step-by-step_guide_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863231 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Mastering_pork_schnitzel_cooking_at_home_A_step-by-step_guide_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863231 320w" width="540" height="720" alt="Mastering pork schnitzel cooking at home A step-by-step guide - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Mastering pork schnitzel cooking at home A step-by-step guide - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-119_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-120_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-122_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The first thing I had to do was prep the pork. I learned that you must pound it really thin with a wooden mallet – like you’re hammering a nail but with more focus! I didn’t want to hit it too hard and accidentally tear the meat, so I had to balance it right. Flattening the pork is supposed to make it tender, and it felt fantastic to see the piece get bigger and thinner as I worked on it. Then, I added some salt and pepper to bring out the flavour. Prepping the pork was already feeling like a workout!</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-124_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-125_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-126_ pf-heading-1-h3">Making it crunchy – The three-step coating process</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863476" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863476 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_1000x.png?v=1729863476 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Easy_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_first-time_cooks_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863476 320w" width="1000" height="1000" alt="Easy pork schnitzel recipe for first-time cooks - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Easy pork schnitzel recipe for first-time cooks - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-128_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-129_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-131_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">This was probably my favourite part – making the schnitzel coating! The recipe calls for a three-step coating process to get that famous schnitzel crunch. First, I coated the pork in flour, which helped the next layer stick. Then, I dunked it into a bowl of beaten eggs, making sure every part was covered. Finally, I rolled it in breadcrumbs, pressing them in to ensure they stayed put. The breadcrumbs make the schnitzel crispy and crunchy, and I was already imagining the sound it would make when I bit into it!</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-133_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-134_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-135_ pf-heading-1-h3">Frying and oven finishing for perfect cooking</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Your_step-by-step_guide_to_delicious_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863535" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Your_step-by-step_guide_to_delicious_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863535 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Your_step-by-step_guide_to_delicious_pork_schnitzel_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863535 320w" width="540" height="720" alt="Your step-by-step guide to delicious pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Your step-by-step guide to delicious pork schnitzel - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-137_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-138_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-140_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">With the pork all coated, it was time to fry! The recipe mentioned avocado oil, but we only had olive oil, so I went with that. I heated the oil in a pan until it sizzled, then carefully placed the schnitzel. It started to bubble and crackle right away, which was so satisfying! Frying each side took a few minutes to get golden brown, but to ensure it was cooked all the way through, we finished it in the oven. Since pork has to be fully cooked, this extra oven time was necessary for safety (and also for extra crispiness!).</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-142_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-143_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-144_ pf-heading-1-h3">Choosing sides, including potatoes</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Best_beginner_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_a_crispy_finish_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863592" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Best_beginner_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_a_crispy_finish_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863592 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Best_beginner_pork_schnitzel_recipe_for_a_crispy_finish_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863592 320w" width="540" height="720" alt="Best beginner pork schnitzel recipe for a crispy finish - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Best beginner pork schnitzel recipe for a crispy finish - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-146_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-147_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-149_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Once the schnitzel was ready, it was time to think about sides. My family chose boiled potatoes and green vegetables, along with a parsley sauce on the side. If I could choose, I’d probably go for fries or mashed potatoes, but I figured I’d give boiled potatoes a try. The green vegetables were a nice pop of colour, and the parsley sauce added a bit of freshness. To be honest, I don’t remember much about the sauce (I was too focused on the schnitzel), but it was fun to try something different.</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-151_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-152_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-153_ pf-heading-1-h3">Final rating - The good, the crispy, and the could-be-crispier</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Homemade_schnitzel_tips_for_a_crunchy_golden_coating_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863683" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Homemade_schnitzel_tips_for_a_crunchy_golden_coating_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863683 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/Homemade_schnitzel_tips_for_a_crunchy_golden_coating_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863683 320w" width="540" height="720" alt="Homemade schnitzel tips for a crunchy, golden coating - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Homemade schnitzel tips for a crunchy, golden coating - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-kWtorq hnOOBS pf-155_ pf-image-1"/><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-156_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image from Jaden the Explorer</p><p class="sc-gFVuLS jpmtwg pf-158_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Looking back, I’d give my first pork schnitzel experience a solid eight out of ten. It turned out nice and crispy on the outside, but if I’m honest, I think it could’ve been even crispier. The flavour was pretty good, and I was happy with the seasoning, but I think I’d change a few things next time. For one, I’d probably plan my ingredients a little better to avoid last-minute changes, like switching out avocado oil for olive oil. And if I get to pick the sides, I’d definitely go for fries or mashed potatoes – much more my style!</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-dhKdPU hjOBND pf-160_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;--s-md:5px;--s-lg:0px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-eBHgEO bnCcLn pf-161_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kAkozD kgiAhT pf-162_ pf-heading-1-h3">Lessons learned and what’s next</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_Make_Pork_Schnitzel_at_Home_Simple_steps_for_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863071" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_Make_Pork_Schnitzel_at_Home_Simple_steps_for_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK.png?v=1729863071 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/How_to_Make_Pork_Schnitzel_at_Home_Simple_steps_for_success_-_The_Mandatory_Training_Group_UK_500x.png?v=1729863071 320w" width="540" height="720" alt="How to Make Pork Schnitzel at Home – Simple steps for success - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="How 